ascents.comment: I mean, I don't know. I was going to do a soft second go on this boy, but then it got harder and harder and harder, and the sense of invincibility that comes with being a Pearl-flasher began to fade into the background of my sad sad soul. I gave up. We left. But I didn’t forget about the Pearl Necklace. And so late in the night, we came back. I tried again. It was still hard. I gave up again. I really gave up this time. “I give up,” I said, staring at my sad sad hands. But then, in the dark nihilism of the desert night (which later became a dessert night, on behalf of Sherlock's birthday), I pulled onto that boy one final time, because why not? Why not do it? And then – with a sea of randos cheering me on (how nice of them?) – I climbed the whole entire thing. My fingertip split in two, but heck – I did the Pearl Necklace. And it was soft.

ascents.comment: I'm drunk because my sciatic nerve short circuited on the "Unnamed Sloper to Lip" on the back of the Leary Bard boulder and rosé takes pain away.  Rosé wine. It's pink. I'm a waffle. I used to love horrible boulders but now I just think some of them make me want to cry. Boulders. Tears. Catharsis. Deep thoughts. Rosé. I don't know if this boulder was hard or not. Fuck. I don't even know Howard Carter.
